                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of this conversation has been found. The information set forth
                    above regarding the hour of the meeting and the participants is taken from
                    Nelson, p. 185; the date of January 3 is derived from Churchill’s telegram of
                    January 4 to Attlee, reporting on the results of various meetings on supply
                    issues (<hi rend="italic">The Grand Alliance</hi>, p. 690). According to
                    Nelson’s account, the discussion concerned <pb facs="0233" n="159"
                        xml:id="pg_159"/> the raising of production estimates for munitions of war,
                    particularly Roosevelt’s goals of 45,000 tanks and 60,000 planes which
                    “startled” Nelson.</p>
            </div>
